HEADWORD: Gestour
<hw>Ges"tour</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Gest</er> a
deed.]</ety> <def>A reciter of gests or legendary tales; a
story-teller.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Minstrels and <qex>gestours</qex> for to tell tales.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gestural</ent>⟦br⟧
